~
8 2097152 16385
0 0 0 0
5 100 0
E
book~
Flipping through the pages, you see the same old stories of Midgaard you
have heard over and over since you were a child. Some history. You are
about to toss the book away when you notice the last page. It seems to
be a transcription of something...in an archaic form of common. Stumbling
over the words, you are pleasantly surprised to learn something new...
~
E
page last~
Day of Thunder, 24th day of the Month of the Dragon, 1010 YH

Tomorrow we leave for the Shadow Grove, the ten of us.  Erinys assures us that
this grove has much natural magic, and we shall again be able to work more
powerful spells than in this miserable city.  We shall raise a new tower
there, and compile a new library of Magecraft.  Alas for the Guild in Thalos
...such horrible loss of knowledge.  750 years of study, gone in a single day
of flame.  Who would have thought that the slaves would revolt? The city
had gone soft on them...treating them as though they were real people, not
the cattle they are.  How dare they burn our city...we who created them!
So few of us survived.  With each year that passes, Mayor Leander listens
to our council less.  We shall see...after we leave we shall see how long
it takes for them to come crawling to us.  We are the last of the Mages of
Thalos, but we will not be taken for granted!

Cyril, Grand Master of Magic.
~
